<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="657" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Walter S. Robertson</persName>, at
                                Peiping</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-09">9 July 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1084. Orders to field forces is subject, 1062 and 1077<note n="97" xml:id="d657fn97">Telegrams of July 6 and 8, <ref target="#pg_1307">pp. 1307</ref> and <ref target="#pg_1326">1326</ref>,
                                respectively.</note> refers. I learned from General Chou this
                            afternoon that Chairman Mao reiterated June 7th orders to all Communist
                            commanders in Manchuria and China on 1 July 1946.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>